## Article CRUD — Backend

### List Published Articles (GET /api/v1/articles)
Support these query params — always apply `status = 'Published' AND deleted_at IS NULL`:
- `?sort=title|created_at` (default: `created_at`)
- `?order=asc|desc` (default: `desc`)
- `?search=keyword` (ILIKE search on `title`)
- `?page=1&limit=20` (pagination)

```typescript
async listPublished(filters: ArticleFilters): Promise<PaginatedResult<ArticleWithMeta>> {
  return articleRepository.findPublished(filters);
}
```

### List Own Articles (GET /api/v1/articles/mine)
- Returns all statuses (Draft / Pending / Published / Rejected) for the authenticated user
- Include `reviewer_feedback` field so author can see rejection reason

### Rich Text Storage
- Store TipTap content as **JSON** (the `JSONContent` type from TipTap)
- Never store as HTML in the database (HTML is generated at render time)
- Provide a utility: `extractTextFromTipTap(json: JSONContent): string` for AI quiz generation

```typescript
// src/lib/tiptap.ts
import { generateText } from '@tiptap/core';
import StarterKit from '@tiptap/starter-kit';

export function extractTextFromTipTap(json: JSONContent): string {
  return generateText(json, [StarterKit]);
}
```

### Delete Rules
| Deleter | Target Status | Action |
|---------|--------------|--------|
| Author | Draft only | Soft delete (`deleted_at = NOW()`) |
| Admin | Any status | Soft delete by default; hard delete available |
- All delete actions require a confirmation pop-up (frontend)

